[assistant] You're right — that test was invalid for `commons-io:2.2`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - In `commons-io:2.2`, `ClassLoaderObjectInputStream.resolveClass(...)` does **not** catch `ClassNotFoundException`.
[assistant] - Its bytecode is effectively:
[assistant]   - `Class.forName(name, false, classLoader)`
[assistant]   - then only `super.resolveClass(...)` if the result were `null`
[assistant] - But `Class.forName(...)` throws on failure; it does not return `null`.
[assistant] - So the `ObjectInputStream#resolveClass(...)` fallback path is not realistically reachable in `2.2`.
[assistant] 
[assistant] That fallback only exists in later versions such as `2.11.0`, where `ClassNotFoundException` is caught explicitly.
[assistant] 
[assistant] I removed the failing test and committed the fix:
[assistant] 
[assistant] - Commit: `5b54d2d58`
[assistant] - Message: `Remove unsupported commons-io 2.2 fallback test`
[assistant] 
[assistant] So the `2.2` test file is back to covering only the reachable paths.
[assistant-event] text_end
